<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-03-31T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-03-31T07:00:00-05:00" n="281" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/526: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-31T20:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">March 31,
                                        1927—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 31—10:10
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>307. Following additional information American consul at Swatow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“All Americans in outlying districts now concentrated and being
                                    held in Swatow except six Catholic missionaries in Kay [garbled
                                    group] district; they have been urged to leave. Local conditions
                                    remain quiet.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>